==English==
===Etymology===
From German [[Schrecklichkeit]], literally ‘awfulness’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈʃrɛklɪçkaɪt/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# A military policy of terrorising an enemy, especially through its civilian population.
# A general atmosphere or situation of awfulness or dread.
#*'''1973''': I embarked on the quotidian '''''schrecklichkeit''''' of getting up. — Kyril Bonfiglioli, ''Don't Point That Thing at Me'' (Penguin 2001, p. 11)